There is a zone in the Rodopi mountains in Bulgaria where people often disappear without a trace, the government is unsurprisingly suppressing some information.

Experienced hikers and villagers with 30+ years of navigating the forests have gone missing with zero footprints left

The USSR had an unknown central cryptozoology bureau where all reports of cryptids were sent to be researched and documented. 

Veselin Durchev was a Bulgarian man who photographed footprints left by an alleged bigfoot sighting in the above area, which were confirmed to be true.
no there are lots of villages there are no uncontacted tribes in the balkans

There are places in the mountain called "dark/damp" where the locals never go, because they believe them to be dangerous and that evil creatures lurk there

I will proceed to translate a story published by an anonymous doctor who had an experience walking through the area yrs ago

He was called to a village to help with a sick cow, it was a sunny October day so he decided to go by foot, the path was along a river (!!!), and suddenly he got the weird feeling that something was not right and he was being watched

he looked back and saw a large furry...

...creature standing in the treeline and watching him. He suddenly was seized by a feeling that everything around him was "not real", like he had found himself in another dimension.

He hurried up and the creature calmly followed from behind, he went as fast as possible and ...

exited the "dark" forest area, after looking back he saw the creature did not exit the treeline but remained there. He felt safe and also felt some weird kind of sadness for it. End of story.

***

The locals at the village apparently knew of such things, called "bear people"

In 2015 an old woman called the 911 hotline to report that she saw a big apelike creature in front of her house, apparently making some screams/howls and digging for something, before seeing her and running away

A man made another report of seeing the same thing a few days later
I actually plan to do so

There is an old folk song in the Rodopi mountain people:

"A bear man is walking through the dark forest"

There was a report of a bunch of gypsy lumberjacks who said they say a large hairy creature in the depths of the forest, watching them from a distance from the treeline

In 2018 Jamal (62 year old local, knew the area well) went missing. He had problems with one of his feet so he was walking slow.

Dogs were unable to pick up his scent and even though the entire area was searched there were zero traces of him found, it was a national mystery

Two months later his corpse was randomly discovered in the same area, even though the search teams found nothing in that same place after his disappearance. Conclusions obvious. 

Ending the thread for now, have a bit more info but will keep collecting stories, maybe visit myself
